  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy roast potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1645529313679-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1645529313679-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1645529313679-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1645529313679-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1645529313679-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are roasting, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1645529315382-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1645529315382-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1645529315382-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1645529315382-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1645529315382-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>lemon halves</strong> (cut-side down) and cook for 3-4 min or until caramelised, then set aside for later, reserving the pan</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1645529318173-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1645529318173-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1645529318173-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1645529318173-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1645529318173-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust a clean tray or plate with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour </strong>and season with a big pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Dip your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into the<strong> seasoned flour</strong> until both sides are well coated and shake off any excess flour</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1645529322108-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1645529322108-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1645529322108-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1645529322108-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1645529322108-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wipe out the reserved pan with kitchen paper, then return to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to coat the bottom of the pan)</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa fillet[s]</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>Venetian-style breaded basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1645529324495-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1645529324495-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1645529324495-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1645529324495-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1645529324495-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, trim, then add your <strong>green beans</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the beans are tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside until later</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1645529326982-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1645529326982-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1645529326982-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1645529326982-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1645529326982-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is cooked, add your <strong>clotted cream</strong> to the pan</p><p>Squeeze in the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>caramelised lemon halves </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>lemon sauce</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining caramelised lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1645529330363-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1645529330363-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1645529330363-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1645529330363-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1645529330363-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Venetian-style breaded basa</strong> with the<strong> crispy roast potatoes</strong> and <strong>green beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> lemon sauce</strong> all over the fish</p><p>Garnish with a<strong> caramelised lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
